                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, my brother plays a Cleric that practicaly levels so that he can duel me and win. I guess he figures that if I can whoop him in real life he could at least have me in the game. I dont want that to happen. 
<br />
I brag on and on about how awesome Enchanters are and how uber of a class we are.
<br />
Now it has been years since we have last dueled and yesterday we started a heated debate with each other on who would win in a duel now. At the moment, naturally, he would win (being level 54 while myself level 42). But I thought that in the future, it would be the other way around.
<br />
Well, I had, of course, defeated him in the debate and made him rather angry until our dad joined. 
<br />
He started giving all of these tips to my brother and I couldnt think of one thing to do in response. Dad suggested to put a 6hp dot that lasts for quite awhile on himself so mezz would not stick. THEN told him how he could cast cancel magic on a charmed mob so it would turn around and attack me. 
<br />
Now I am angry at dad at the moment because he is always giving tips to my brother and not me, and I am desperately wanting to proove them wrong. Please help me.. I dont know what to do!
<br />
Lol. Sincerily,
<br />
Nilmarth N'ilanthir
<br />
Ancient Art of Shadows
<br />
The Tribunal</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
