                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd say go with your animation. Better than dealing with an ornery pet that breaks charm. Plus the constant melee / bashing of the pet will play havoc with a cleric.
<br />

<br />
After you get hit once and your pet is wailing away, cast tash (and hope brother doesn't know that cure poison gets rid of tash <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />), and then eye of confusion (blind spell). Doubt your brother will have cure blindness up and ready to go, so you have some free time to plot at this point.
<br />

<br />
So what to do next? Annul magic like the wind. If you've allowed pre buffing, then get rid of all those pesky HP and AC buffs clerics get. Then start cycling through your debuff dots, tossing in a cripple as well. Your brother won't even be able run toward you because he'll have 1 strength. Just be sure to keep on the edge of his casting range (so you can quickly jump outside his range when he starts to cast) and load up on your stun spells (including Whirl Till You Hurl and your stun Nukes).
<br />

<br />
Should hopefully be able to finish him off that way. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
