                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think most of these suggestions depend on you being somewhere near the same level.
<br />

<br />
The strategies have to depend on what you each have available to cast. If your brother has uber resists (which will be unlikely at mid-50s) you're going to be in trouble. I've never PvP'ed, so take what I have to say with a grain of salt, but what I've read from enchanters who pvp a great deal is to cast strip enchantments, then mana sieve, then strip, then sieve, then strip, then sieve for all you're worth and let your animation beat up on him. And toss in a tash and a slow somewhere. Without mana and slowed, he would have trouble.
<br />

<br />
However a 42 enchanter vs a 54 cleric is going to have some major problems with resists. The good news is that mana sieve doesn't care (irresistable) and strip enchantments still seems to do an acceptable job.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Max
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=368646" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fanamax the Enchanter</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
