                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you can get into your 60's duelling become a lot easier, then impossible.
<br />

<br />
As chanters our only form of spell is magic based, anyone with an unbuffed MR of about 200 is basically immune to our spells.
<br />

<br />
2 spells that are a must for any PvP. Recant and Rapture.
<br />

<br />
Recant is a -400(resist check) 4 slot debuff.
<br />
Rapture is an unresistable mezz. (there is no level cap on spells in PvP)
<br />

<br />
If you are not of a level to mem these spells then use the next best <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
If a cleric manages to dot themselves and its MR based you can strip the dot with a debuff. If its not then your stuffed for mezzing them.
<br />

<br />
Cleric tactics for PvP are basically melee (that hammer is a pita) and heal. They dont nuke.
<br />

<br />
-------
<br />

<br />
Your tactics.
<br />

<br />
Summon a pet and haste it, buff up, mem your spells, goto the toilet etc <span style="font-style: italic">before</span> you jump into the arena or accept the /d.
<br />

<br />
If the cleric dots themselves and you can't "cure" it. Run around for a few minutes so it wears off.
<br />

<br />
Now you get to mezz them. If you have rapture then dont bother with tash first, rapture will land no matter what their MR is. If you are using regular mezz then you might want to tash first.
<br />

<br />
Once mezzed hit them with your dispells, use the most powerfull ones you have untill mezz is stripped. Recant is good because its almost unresistable. Then re-mezz and cast your debuffs.
<br />

<br />
If you can cripple+weaken your target they will probably be almost rooted. Its about -150 STR and can really hurt if you are carrying a lot of heavy plate armour <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> Slowing them is also amusing, especially if they have a nice proccing hammer. If they debuffed your pet now is a good time to rebuff it (or yourself).
<br />

<br />
After this is where your tactics vary widely. If you reckon you can keep them chain stunned then drop a nice debuff dot on them like asphyxiate. Let them hit you (your pets a sadist that only gets "turned on" when you are in pain) then cycle at least 2 stuns with a 3rd in reserve incase of a resist.
<br />

<br />
If you think that stunning might be dodgy then just mem a nuke and really really annoy them with this trick.
<br />

<br />
Nuke, mezz, nuke, mezz....
<br />

<br />
Subtle it isn't, amusing it is. Mezz will stop them from healing/casting.
<br />

<br />
If they are rooted/snared from your debuffs you dont need to blind them as you will find it easy to stay out of melee. If they have enough STR to aviod that trap then blind is a good way of causing them to not "see" whats going on.
<br />

<br />
If the cleric is clever they will root your pet. Just dispell it to remove root (and haste).
<br />

<br />
If you want to use a mezz to interupt casting then mem your level 4 one. Its so cheap you can chain cast it and see little effect on your mana. This is really handy if they are dotted and trying to heal - but you dont want to get into melee range for a stun to land.
<br />

<br />
Dont bother with charming unless the pet can finish the cleric in a couple of rounds (about 20 secs max). You are more likely to kill yourself otherwise.
<br />

<br />
If you have the time and want to be really evil then keep them at the debuffed/mezzed stage and steal all their mana. When you go for the kill leave a mana dot on them. A caster thats perma rooted and doesn't have enough mana to gate is a very sad sight  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Btw cleric nukes are also MR based, if you can keep yours up high enough then they will almost never land a nuke <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
(edit)
<br />
Forgot to add.
<br />

<br />
Your buffs should include at the minimum Illusion:Fire Elemental - the DS will eat cleric pets in no time.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
