                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just to clarify the dispell thing.
<br />

<br />
The lowest level dispell can strip level 65 buffs.
<br />

<br />
Dispell will <span style="font-style: italic">always</span> land but it will not always strip a buff. Each buff will get a resist check of its own. If it passes then the dispell moves onto the next buff untill it either runs out of buffs or dispells one.
<br />
Some dispells can strip more than 1 buff. In this case the above is still true but it continues untill it runs out of buffs or dispells the set number.
<br />

<br />
This is why when you get hit by a dispell a random buff can dissapear and not just the top ones. If all dispells were unresistable then they would always strip the top buffs first. If dispells were level vs level restricted then it wouldn't matter how many times it was cast, it could never strip a high level spell.
<br />

<br />
Recant is good because not only does it have a neg400 check but strips 4 buffs. And yes i have had recant skip buffs on me before, even though its the best PC castable dispell in the game.
<br />

<br />
Zeks are different in that everyone goes for resists above all else. On the normal "bluebie" servers no one really works on resists unless they have to, or it just happens with gear.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
