                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The only cleric dots are undead ones; so to dot themselves, they must have a clicky or outside help.  Even if dotted, remember that mez interrupts spell casts, and so is a cheap defense.
<br />

<br />
Only clerics above 56 have a proccy hammer.  Almost all of their dps is from procs; pure melee dps is approx 3 dps.  Slow does NOT affect proc rate.  A slowed cleric will proc just as many times per minute as a hasted one.  Don't bother to slow him.
<br />

<br />
He will stun you when he sees a nuke coming; either cast a stun, or bash.  A tashed and rooted cleric can't melee, but can still stun.  The level 54 cleric pet can interrupt you as well, but only has 100 hp, so is easily dismissed.  Their nukes are about the same general damage and recast delay as an enchanter nuke, so if you are going to be nuking, so will they.
<br />

<br />
If you have room to fight, minor illusion is a good way to surprise them, as is invis - they can't cast see invis themselves (but just might have a worn effect).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
