                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The keys to fighting a cleric:
<br />

<br />
1) You will never outdamage his heals.  While he has mana, you cannot win.  Do not do any nukage until he is out of mana.
<br />

<br />
2) Use your animation.  Your animation will provide constant unresistable DPS throughout the fight.  Your goal is to piss off the cleric to the point where he is chasing you around and focusing on YOU while your pet is chewing him up from behind.
<br />

<br />
3) Never Mez.  If you mez him, your animation will stop doing damage.  You always want your animation to be attacking him.
<br />

<br />
4) Debuffing.  The first part of the fight is getting rid of his buffs.  Tash is such a quick cast I would save it for later in the fight.  I always open up with the highest Cancel/strip/recant magic spell you have since it's a longer cast.  You can sneak in a Tash later.  Alternate a few Recants/Cancels in with mana seive and whatever mana tap spell you have at your level.  Seive him dry of mana.  Just run around and Seive while the pet is whacking on him.
<br />

<br />
5) Annoyance.  You want to keep him focused on you so I usually throw in one or two annoyance spells like Blind or Whirl till you hurl.  Both of these spells are EXTREMELY effective on PC's.
<br />

<br />
6) The Kill.  Ok, so now your cleric is buffless, manaless, your pet has him down to half health and he's chasing you with his hammer.  Just nuke the bastard.  Root, Blind, Whirl, hide behind a tree, get some casting time off and nuke him down.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
